The paper deals with the complexity of a graph partitioning problem, which is a common topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The problem involves finding cliques and triangle-free graphs, which are also relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory. The authors also mention the use of reduction techniques, which is a common tool in computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
